What you need to know:

On Wednesday, Mwithiga recollected his lost passion in life, the now rekindled Safari Rally KenyaIt is a killer section, and according to Mwithiga, a graveyard of front bumpers of top cars, which I’m told by Kenya’s Surinder Thatthi, Vice President for Africa at the International Automobile Federation, cost up to Sh900,000, per bumper!There is this 45 degrees killer drift which deputy clerk of course Nazir Yakub continues referring to as “the best of the best."